  "prompt": "I got 753 rank in Aiims and I have not attended to 1 at counseling. will I am eligible for second and third counseling?",
  "response": "If you did not participate in the first round of counseling for AIIMS, you may still be eligible for the second and third rounds, but this typically depends on the specific guidelines and rules set by the AIIMS counseling authorities for that particular year. Generally, candidates who have not secured a seat in the first round or those who have opted for upgradation might be allowed to participate in subsequent rounds.\n\nTo ensure you're following the correct procedure, consider the following steps:\n\n1. **Check the Official AIIMS Website:** Look for any announcements or updates related to counseling rounds. They may provide specific instructions for candidates who missed the first round.\n\n2. **Read the Counseling Brochure:** This document usually contains detailed information on the eligibility criteria and process for each round of counseling.\n\n3. **Contact AIIMS Officials:** If the information is not clear, reaching out directly to the AIIMS counseling helpline or official email may provide clarification.\n\n4. **Stay Alert for Official Notifications:** Make sure you are aware of all deadlines and requirements so you do not miss the opportunity to participate in subsequent rounds.\n\nKeep in mind that procedures may vary from year to year, so it's important to refer to the specific guidelines applicable to your admission cycle.",
